text: Necarne Castle, also known as Castle Irvine, is a Victorian castle near Irvinestown in County Fermanagh, Northern Ireland. The two-storey façade was designed by John B. Keane; work began in 1831. ==See also== *Castles in Northern Ireland ==References== Category:Castles in County Fermanagh Category:Grade B+ listed buildings Category:Register of Parks, Gardens and Demesnes of Special Historic Interest
title: Necarne
